The SteamVR Chaperone component is used to display to the user where the soft and hard bounds of the VR interaction area are. In the following How - To we will take a look at how to add the SteamVR Chaperone to any UE4 VR Pawn.

[REGION:note]
The following How - To is going to make use of the Standing VRPawn with added Motion Controller support. If you are not sure how to set this up the following two How - To's will help you out:
* [Set Up Standing Cameras for SteamVR ](Platforms\SteamVR\HowTo\StandingCamera)
* [Set Up Motion Controllers for SteamVR](Platforms\VR\MotionController)
[/REGION]

[REGION:warning]
It is **NOT** possible nor advisable to disable the Chaperone system from inside UE4. You can, however, adjust how UE4 will react to the user getting close to the boundaries.  
[/REGION]

## SteamVR Chaperone Setup

To add the SteamVR Chaperone system to your UE4 player pawn, you will need to do the following:

1. Open up your projects player Pawn Blueprint and make sure the **Components** tab is visible.  

1. Click on the **Add Component** button and from the displayed list search for the **Steam VRChaperone** component and when located, click on it to add it to the Component list.

	![](SVRChaperone_00.png)

1. When completed, your player pawn should look like the following image.

	![](SVRChaperone_01.png)

1. Now, launh your project in VR and put on your Vive HMD and when you aproach the bounds of your VR interaction area you should see something simialr to the following video.

